                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On February 28, 1950, Chile and the United States reached agreement on a
                    Lend-Lease Settlement Arrangement. The Arrangement was embodied in the Chilean
                    Embassy’s notes of October 17, 1949 and February 28, 1950, and a United States
                    note to the Chilean Embassy of the latter date. (None printed; all filed under
                    725.56/2–2850.) In a note of May 10, 1950, to the Chilean Embassy, the
                    Department stated that Chile, by a payment to the United States of 15 million
                    pesos on April 27, had fulfilled the payment terms of the Settlement Arrangement
                    and discharged its repayment responsibilities under the United States-Chilean
                    Lend-Lease Agreement of March 2, 1943. (725.56/5–1050)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
